-20 03:58:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','In Chronicles, go to the HAR masterfile, and edit category list item #85, the Billing Indicator.  Create a new category list item called \"Undo Billing..\"  Save, recompile, and close.  In Hyperspace, go to Hospital Billing --> Account Maintenance, open an account, click on \"Coll Activities.\" and select \"Set Billing Indicator.\"  A screen will pop up, and towards the bollom there will be the field \"Billing Indicator(s):\".  Click on the ellipses, and select \"Undo Billing.\"  Fill in other fields as appropriate, and click \"accept.\" \r\n\r\nIn the appropriate HB Accountb WQs, delete the non-location-specific inclusion criteria; then, add s criteria \"BILLING INDICATOR = UNDO BILLING.\"',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL- \"Undo Billing\" billing indicator PROD ENVIRONMENT','Billers place a Stop Bill on accounts after they undo billing at HIM  request changes.  The Stop Bill causes the accounts to go into these WQ.  HIM often forgets to remove the stop bill after they have recoded the account. Instead of a stop bill we would like a billing indicator that flows the account to the WQ.  HIM is used to removing billing indicators.  Once they finish with the account and remove the billing indicator it will flow back through the system edits. The billing indicator will also prevent the account from showing in a DNB/STOP BILL WQ until it is ready to be resolved by billers (stop bills will not be removed accidentally by billers) ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(314,2394179,1,1,NULL,1282,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL - PROD Payor/Plan updates',NULL,'2199525, 2326373',NULL,'Tanya Appel',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','M','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-03-14 21:00:00','2008-03-11 15:24:21',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-03-18 08:5