NULL,NULL,'2008-03-17 00:00:00','2008-03-13 00:00:00','2008-03-17 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,37,37,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-04-04 03:16:00','2008-04-19 07:31:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','3/17/2008  Approved NOTE:  Darryl to do: send PPT to Dr Bliss for review; Contact SCAL re their remediation and timing for this issue, forward to Dr. Bliss\r\n','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL RA1318 PROD Spring 07- Clean up Logs Linked to Multiple Patients \n\nWhen logs are created and are not linked to cases, the logs will sometimes use an ID that was previously used by a deleted case.  When that happens, there are multiple patients that look as if they are linked to the same log.\n\nThis Release Authorization will allow Epic to run a utility to unlink the log from the incorrect patient and clean up the patient record so that the log will only remain linked to the correct patient.  The incorrect surgical encounter will be changed to an encounter type of \"Empty\" so that it can be filtered off of Chart Review and not be treated as a surgical encounter.\n\nTesting Instructions\nAfter the utility is run, make sure that the log information no longer displays on the incorrect patient.  This can be done by going to chart review and making sure that the incorrect surgery encounter does not display.  The encounter should now have a type of \"Empty\" or not display.  Also, the log should not display for the incorrect patient in the Patient Station activity.\n\nNCAL NOTES\nThis RA will need to be ran on a weekly basis for data remediation. Epic is still developing a fix that has no ETA, as of this time.  If we do not run this utility on a weekly basis, 2 patients will still potentially appear on one chart.','Remove surgical contact pointers to avoid 2 people displaying on 1 persons chart.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(439,2467410,1,1,NULL,336,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL Cor