nce Options Template, in the                 \n  Attachments\n \n* Divided Payors into two RFC: UNITED HEALTH is on this RFC# 24990404 = Already in SCAL PROD \n   All other Payors are on RFC 2548833','ALLOW THE AUTOMATED POSTING OF 835 INFORMATION','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(583,2503574,1,1,NULL,1380,NULL,NULL,'KPHC- NCAL PROD Run a Tag to auto-population of the AdmitType, Admit Source & Discharge Disposition',NULL,'2443493',NULL,'Vergina Felder',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','M','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-05-21 06:01:00','2008-04-19 10:56:00',NULL,NULL,'SR2443493',NULL,'2008-05-27 05:33:45',NULL,'A','HIMTECH','KPHC CN HIM CODING TECH','Coding & Abstracting Maintenance','End User Applications','KPHC HIM',NULL,NULL,' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,'N',NULL,'A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,581,828,581,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-05-08 00:00:00','2008-05-08 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,157,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-05-07 03:09:00','2008-05-08 03:11:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Need auto-population of the Admission Type, Admission Source & Discharge Disposition on the new HAR when a Guarantor change is made.\n\nThe problem flow is as follows:\n1.	A guarantor change is made by the LBO\n2.	A new HAR is created and combined w/ the old HAR\n3.	The DNB edit of \"Patient Status At Discharge\" is placed on the account because the Admission Type, Admission Source & Discharge Disposition does not auto-populate from the old HAR to the new HAR.\n\n3 EXAMPLES ARE PROVIDED ON THE WORD ATTACHMENT.\n\nPer Epic, a Guarantor change is one example where the info can be copied over:\n----- Forwarded by Vergina Felder/CA/KAIPERM on 03/24/2008 03:25 PM -----\nMatt Beglinger <mbegling@epicsystems.com> \n03/24/2008 02:58 PM	\n	To\n	Vergina Felder/CA/KAIPERM@KAIPERM\n	cc\n	\n	Subject\n	RE: SR #2417243\nVergie,\n \nChanging an account class will not create a new HAR.  The trouble with this account was that a user created an account 31211294001 and the account was coded.  After the account was coded a user (VELASQUEZ, ASH) went back into the ADT/patient stay and created a new hospital account.  What the system does in this case is mark the old HAR as combined and create a new HAR that will need to be recoded.  We would need to follow up with the user to see why they created a new HAR.  You can change the account class on a HAR without creating a new HAR.  To edit the account class they should go to ADT Event Management.  This will update the account/patient class without creating a new HAR which means we will retain the coding information.\n \nWe do copy the coding info forward in certain circumstances.  On such example is guarantor changes.  When we change a guarantor we will copy the coding information form the old HAR to the new HAR but in all other circumstances the accounts need to be recoded.\n \nThanks\nMatt\n\nThis request is for the system to auto-populate all the needed information to the coding info tab from the new HAR from the old HAR on Guarantor changes.','This auto-population will help drive the bill out the door faster, impacting both HIM and Resolute','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(584,2548662,1,1,NULL,1418,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL - PROD Payor/Plan updates for May',NULL,'2481155',NULL,'Tanya Appel',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','M','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-05-30 21:00:00','2008-05-06 10:40:41',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-06-03 05:35:04',NULL,'A','RESLUTTC','KPHC CN RESOLUTE TECH','Maintenance','End User Applications','KPHC Billing (Resolute)',NULL,