log and going forward bill for the non-covered charges, it will be necessary to move the patient liability aka non-covered charges from the insurance bucket to the self pay bucket.  An Epic Property Edit exist E754662 that will NRP the copay charges, so that it can move down the self pay path and be billed.   \n\nHB Resolute completed the build for the Property Edit, yet left it inactive within KPHC; Epic TS ran audit reports for PBS OPS, and a release schedule was developed. \n\nOver the course of Four Days: \n\nRules: \n1.  Routing Rule: to identify the Non-Billable Payors (KP Classic, KP Medicare Risk, KP MCAL, excluding Inter-Regional in NCAL) \n2.  Criteria: Activate Property Edit E754662 to NRP the Patient Liability from the Insurance Bucket to the Self Pay Bucket. \n3.  Bucket Balance should be > $0. \n4.  Bucket Status: must be either = Created or Outstanding\n5.  Bucket Type: Must be either Primary or Secondary Claim. \n\nSystem Actions: \n#1 First System Action: Based on the Rules, create a system action transfer to Self Pay for discharge dates greater than 12/31/07 (2008-Current), per this schedule:  \nA statement will be sent out for the remaining self pay portion in the self pay bucket. \n\nRun #1:  South Bay\nRun #2:  Central\nRun #3:  North Bay\nRun #4:  East Bay\nRun #5:  Capital \nRun #6:  Golden Gate\nRun #7:  CC\n\nCreate a Stop Bill = CBO Non-Covered Soft Cap Remediation April, 2008. \n\nSystem Action #2: \n\nh)	Create a system action using the same criteria as #1, except for discharge dates prior to 01/01/08\ni)	Add the Stop Bill CBO Non-Covered Soft Cap Remediation April, 2008 \nj)	 \"Hold\" to allow the charges to marry up with any self pay payment etc.,\nk)	Create another system action to Wr','Prevent the self pay portion from capitating with ins bucket','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(640,2539781,1,1,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'#KPHC NCAL PROD: Install 3 adhocs for ePremis to Reso