itation adjustments.  This led to accounts being capitated multiple times and ending up with credit balances if the batch was run multiple times\n\nNow, New programming points have been developed that will allow these capitation adjustments that are marked inappropriately to be fixed by either reversing them off the account or by marking/tracking them as capitation adjustments.\n\nApproved by Tim McDermott, PBS OPS and Karen Kretz, Finance.','Correct Credit Balances resulting from Soft Capitation Build','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(715,2659707,1,1,NULL,1490,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL - PROD - Update existing DNB to error any account base class of Emergency missing a 450 rev code for ER to INP.',NULL,'2558986',NULL,'Bill Butler',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','CM',NULL,NULL,NULL,'A','N','N','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-07-16 06:00:00','2008-06-16 12:48:19',NULL,NULL,'RFC 1769535',NULL,'2008-08-01 12:40:16',NULL,'A','RESLUTTC','KPHC CN RESOLUTE TECH','Change Request','End User Applications','KPHC Billing (Resolute)',NULL,NULL,' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,'N',NULL,'A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,583,891,583,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-06-19 00:00:00','2008-07-02 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,131,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-06-16 04:27:00','2008-07-02 03:07:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','6/19:  Test RFC missing MCV in worklog. \r\n7/2:  Above provided. Setting to Approved. ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL - Update existing DNB = Emergency Room Charges are Missing to include not only ER Claims, but extend to ER to INP Conversions.  The DNB should Error any Account Base Class of Emergency that is Missing a Revenue Code of 450 and any Account Base Class of Inpatient that has any one of the admission sources listed