ready editing some data in the lower portion.  If you go ahead with this selection, that data will be lost.  Are you sure you want to go ahead?\n5.       Click the \"No\" button.\n6.       The Implant B information will stay in the fields below, but the Implant A row will stay highlighted in the grid above.\n7.       If you click \"File\" with Implant A still highlighted above, it will replace Implant A with the information that you were filling out for Implant B.\n \nThe Fix is two part. 1. Replace Current Print group LPG 30068410 with LPG 68412 in report #50268104 in Lead and propagate the report. 2. Change the settings in System Def > Settings 3 > Log Entry implant name default criteria and set #1 to INVENTORY ITEM - LOG ID and #2 to INVENTORY ITEM - SERIAL NUMBER','Fix for patient safety issue.  Ensure that implant information is not lost.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(982,2909227,1,1,NULL,408,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL: SA level Event Notification build for PCP InBasket (NB, CA, EB require)',NULL,'2876185',NULL,'Wenzel/Yu for pilot implementati',NULL,NULL,'ADT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','0',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-17 06:00:00','2008-09-10 13:05:58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-22 05:34:34',NULL,'A','ADTTECH','KPHC CN ADT TECH','Configuration Change','End User Applications','KPHC Admit Discharge Transfer (ADT)',NULL,NULL,' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'A',NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,'N',NULL,'A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,774,945,774,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2008-09-18 00:00:00','2008-09-18 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,178,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-09-15 09:48:00','2008-09-18 03:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Change authorized for 9/17/08 - include w/ monthly release. Testing reqs waived. Change made for AMB, bu