pen RA for Epic to switch from .1 to EID.\n\nTested in RFC2996226\nThere is no impact to PROD if this RFC fails because it is being executed off hours on a weekend when Resolute Coders are not working.  They will take a full backup and will reimport if the RFC fails so normal business will not be interrupted.\n\nIt must be added that this change does not affect the functionality of Resolute or any other HealthConnect application.  This has no affect on Patient Safety or Medical Documentation, because messages occur as a result of charges posting into Resolute.  These charges are posted after services have been performed for patients.  No information in Resolute is sent back to the Medical Record.\n\nInformation sent from Resolute to Ingenix is for the purposes of verifying that charge information is correct and compliant with billing.  Again this information has no affect on the Medical Record and all processes are after services have been performed.\n\nIt should also be added that SCAL performed this change successfuly in their Production environments in June of this year.','Consistency of data being sent to Ingenix','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(1147,3058430,1,1,NULL,1759,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL  PROD  Resolute RMO configurations, testing and implementation for NCAL Self Funding and CSI',NULL,'2603509',NULL,'Michael Boehm',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'r',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','EM',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,'2008-11-04 18:00:00','2008-11-19 06:00:00','2008-10-29 09:44:35',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-24 05:32:12',NULL,'A','RESLUTTC','KPHC CN RESOLUTE TECH','Configuration Change','End User Applications','KPHC Billing (Resolute)',NULL,NULL,' ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'N','Y','N',NULL,'N',NULL,'A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,740,820,740,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2008-11-03 00:00:00','2008-10-30 00