roval?','Change Authorized for Production on 6/17/09, per (Larry Cole) ','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL PROD - Cadence - Need new column added to the Shedule Orders Tab for Radiology to show Terminated Providers\n\nRad orders can not be changed if the provider is terminated.  This is an issue for Radiant because ordering providers order Modality Orders.  Modality Orders are really just place setters.  They have no CPT codes attached.  The order must be updated/changed to the actual order that the Radiologist protocols.  If the provider is terminated, this order can not be updated, i.e. a CT order needs to be udpated/changed to a CT Head with Contrast.  Having the Terminated Provider Column will inform the RAD receptionist prior to checkin.','If the receptionist does not know the provider is terminated, in some cases the problem is not found until the patient is on the table.  This is problematic because now they have to get a new order in the system and they have to find a doctor willing to enter the order.  If the receptionist knew in advance, they could have the problem fixed before the patient arrives. ','2009-06-11 - Karin D Gregg - Testing Approved/Change Authorized<BR><BR>2009-06-11 - Margaret Askew - per phone call with joel, routine<BR><BR>2009-06-16 - Larry E Cole - Change Authorized for Production on 6/17/09<BR><BR>2009-06-16 - Margaret Askew - routine<BR><BR>2009-06-16 - Remedy Application Service - Approval process complete. James H OGorman, has been notified approval<BR><BR>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(1810,3731223,1,1,NULL,2201,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL RCSI- PROD Inactivate Radiopharms-Radiant Router WQs Inactivation after Go-Live validation. Production only',NULL,'3699536',NULL,'John McRedmond',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Clo','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'R',NULL,NULL,'A','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','EM',NULL,NULL,NULL,'S','N','N','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,'2009-06-17 12:13:47','2009-07-0