 built in WITS2*\r\n*Routine Change added to RFC summary*','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NC PROD - Change configuration for TMV EKG charges to bill only TC component. If the charge is attached to an admitted  HAR and the charge is triggered prior to the TMV final result, change the procedure to 93005.  This is the TC charge and will post to the HAR. This logic does not apply to charges for MOB or HOV patients. In addition, a rule will be placed in the TMV Charge Router Audit WQ to catch any TMV charges for an MOB or HOV location where the charge is triggered prior to the final result.','TMV charges are being tirggered prior to the final read by the Cardiologist. In this case the professsional component of the charge is not billable. This is a problem with the charge triggering process that the IP Clinical team is working on. In the interium we will not bill for the professional component of these charges.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(2188,4141612,1,1,NULL,2408,NULL,NULL,'RTM-CBO Steady State Implementation - PB Account WQs for Collections activity',NULL,'4017964',NULL,'Bill Butler',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Pen','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'R',NULL,NULL,'N','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','EM',NULL,NULL,NULL,' ','N','N','N','M','N','N',NULL,NULL,'2009-12-15 18:00:00','2009-12-23 23:00:00','2009-10-12 18:15:58',NULL,'2009-12-16 22:00:00',NULL,NULL,'2009-12-13 23:05:20',NULL,'PA','RESLUTTC','KPHC CN RESOLUTE TECH','Workqueues','End User Applications','KPHC Billing (Resolute)',NULL,NULL,' ','Approval',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Y',NULL,'N','N','N',NULL,'N',NULL,'A',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,574,504,574,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1900-01-01 00:00:00','2009-12-03 00:00:00','2009-12-03 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,171,140,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-12 06:22:00','2009-12-03 03:21:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','*12/3:\r\n1. Nothing attached to RFC.\r\n\r\n','The CBO is expecting this change and have realigned labor policies to match it.  The notification is all happening in SCAL, which is where all the employees are who work these queues. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'CBO Steady State Implementation - PB Account WQs for Collections activity\n\nThese changes will mostly be deactivations to WQs that are no longer needed.  In Prod, users will need to empty these before the inactivation. We need not do the same in test - especially since they will not be as populated.\n\nName changes are something else that really does not need testing.  We just change the name.\n\nThere are a small number of WQ rule changes. Those will be what testing targets.  There will be some manual batch job running to do this, but that is not difficult.\n\nThe long implemenation timeline is there to provide time for checking and verifying the changes.  That cannot happen overnight.','These WQ changes need to be implemented to support the new design for the CBO and its collection efforts.  While the term \"steady state\" may not really apply, there are labor changes taking place that will rely on this new setup.  As a result, we need to implement the changes as quickly as time and testing allow. ','2009-12-03 - Melanie M Kramme - Testing Approved/Change Authorized<BR><BR>2009-12-03 - Margaret Askew - ROUTINE<BR><BR>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(2189,4143724,1,1,NULL,2409,NULL,NULL,'KPHC NCAL HB PROD - Acct WQs Setup for HOV Depts',NULL,'4099026',NULL,'*',NULL,NULL,'RSLT','Pla','RC','N',NULL,NULL,'R',NULL,NULL,'N','A',NULL,'SR',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'L','EM',NULL,NULL,NULL,' ','N','N','N','L','N','N',NULL,NULL,'2009-10-16 09:30:00','2009-10-16 19:00:00','2009-10-13 11:17:14',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2009-10-14 15:45:58',NULL,'AR','RESLUTTC','KPHC CN RESOLUTE TECH','Workqueues','End User Applications','KPHC Billing (Resolute)',NULL,NULL,' 2.00','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,N