rder class is specified as \"OHSS\" and the orders are pended for the physician to sign\n3. Physician signs the orders\n4. Patient goes to the lab to get bloodwork\n5. Patient presents to the clinic \"OHS DEPT\" for an appointment with the physician afterwards (sometimes the same day, many times 1-7 days later)\nSince the orders are almost 100% done in an Ancillary order encounter, when the pt. is checked in at the lab through Scheduled orders, the visit type defaults to LABCORP which is correct, but the account defaults to the P/F account. The receptionist would need to select the correct account which should be CORP. There has been some issues with patient getting billed because the wrong account is selected. In order to prevent inaccurate billing, it would be best if a Hard Stop error message is added each time the wrong account is selected based on the Visit Type. (Just like workers comp it does for Workers Comp orders). \nThis request has been approved by both Dept. Mngrs, Directors, and Chiefs. \n\nPlease feel free to give me a call with any questions. \n\nMatrix of order classes that map to visit types is attached.  this Matrix applies over all to order class/visit type and is larger scope than this SR request.\n\nADD LABCORP VISIT TYPE TO EXISTING RULE - \"NCAL VISIT TYPE OHSS WITH CORP ACCOUNT\".  \n- Tracy Franklin - 10/12/09\n\n\nThere are additional requirements:\n\nWith ImagCorp VT require corporate account\nWith LabWC VT require WC account\nWith LabResearch VT require copay override of \"KFHP Med Group   Policy\"\nWith ImagResearch VT require copay override of \"KFHP med Group Policy\"\nW','This will prevent incorrect selection of accounts','2009-12-16 - Caroline W Rogers - Testing Approved / Changed Authorized<BR><BR>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Test Comment NCF',NULL),(2353,4080829,1,1,NULL,2379,NULL,NULL,'RTM-KPHC/NCAL  (PROD)  PROOF OF CONCEPT - Configure HB & PB RMO for Trust/Commerce Credit card fi